HEADWORD: fudge factor
<hw>fudge factor</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a term or factor inserted into
a calculation to compensate for anticipated errors, or to arbitrarily
make the result conform to some desired conclusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

